Record Class LogProperties.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
io.jstach.rainbowgum.LogProperties.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter
Record Components:
prefix - added to the key before looking up in LogProperties.
search - if true will recursively search up the key path
All Implemented Interfaces:
LogProperties.PropertyGetter<String>
Enclosing interface:
LogProperties.PropertyGetter<T>
public static record LogProperties.PropertyGetter.RootPropertyGetter(String prefix, boolean search) extends Record implements LogProperties.PropertyGetter<String>
A property getter and builder that has no conversion but may prefix the key and search recursively up the key path.

While you can map the string properties with LogProperties.PropertyGetter.map(PropertyFunction) it is preferred to use the to methods on this class for basic types especially for list or map types as the implementation will call the implementation specific in LogProperties. An example is toMap() which will call the LogProperties implementration of LogProperties.mapOrNull(String).
